<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-768-169  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 768 169.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Dec 24 1990 v24 n52-53 p6(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Pacifying the power-hungry: tips for handling MIPS-gobbling userswithout breaking your IS budget. (information systems)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Slater, Derek.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Information resources managers face the challenge of providingmore powerful equipment and more extensive services to demandingusers without exceeding an ever-tightening budget.andP;  Among the mostdemanding user departments are the customer service, accounting,administration, marketing and sales sectors.andP;  The rise in userdemand corresponds to a growing awareness of the gains technologycan offer the busy professional.andP;  These users are seeking acompetitive edge.andP;  MIS managers can diffuse the pressure byhelping users to provide for some of their own needs, teachingthem to retrieve information and giving them technical supportinstruction.andP;  Remote support can be another crucial function inreducing the demands on the MIS staff.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     MISBudgetingUser RelationsComputer industryResource allocation.andO;Feature:   illustrationcartoon.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>